Package com.microsoft.azure.cognitiveservices.inkrecognizer.model

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    InkBullet
    The InkBullet class represents the collection of one or more ink strokes that were recognized as a bullet point on a line
    InkDrawing
    The InkShape class represents the collection of one or more ink strokes that were recognized as a drawing/shape
    InkList
    The InkList class represents the collection of one or more ink strokes that were recognized as a list.
    InkRecognitionRoot
    The InkRecognitionRoot class is the root of the model result tree from the Ink Recognizer service.
    InkRecognitionUnit
    The InkRecognitionUnit class represents a single entity recognized by the InkRecognizer service.
    InkWord
    The InkWord class represents a collection of one or more ink strokes that were recognized as a word.
    Line
    The Line class represents the collection of one or more ink strokes that were recognized as a line
    Paragraph
    The Paragraph class represents the collection of one or more ink strokes that were recognized as a paragraph
    Point
    The Point class unlike the InkPoint interface represents a single geometric position on a plane.
    Rectangle
    The Rectangle class is used to deliver the bounding rectangle of a recognition unit.
    WritingRegion
    The WritingRegion represents a certain part of a writing surface that the user has written at least one word on.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    InkRecognitionUnitKind
    The InkRecognitionUnitKind has all the different categories of model units available from the service.
    Shape
    The Shape enum represents different shapes that can be reported by the ink recognizer service.
